<span id="SENTENCE_65">At this very time Melissa is dancing with the prettiest gentleman; she will breakfast with him to-morrow, and then run to two auctions, and hear compliments, and have presents; then she will be dressed and visit, and get a ticket to the play, then go to cards, and win, and come home with two flambeaus before her chair.</span>
<span id="SENTENCE_66">Dear Mr. Rambler, who can bear it?</span>
